--------------------------------Interview Basics-------------------------------------
1. Difference between def and lambda.
def :- It creates a named function with multiple statements.

lambda :- It is an anonymous single-line function



#2. Difference between map() and filter().
map():- It applies a function to all elements of an iterable and returns
the transformed values.

filter() :- It applies a function to all elements of an iterable and returns
the transformed values.



#3. Difference between filter() and list comprehension.
filter() :- returns elements of an iterable that satisfy a condition using a function.

list comprehension :- It can filter and transform elements in a single, more flexible
expression.




#4. Why reduce() is not a built-in function in Python?
--> It reduce() is not a built-in in Python 3 because its use is less common and can
be replaced by clearer loops or comprehensions.

--> it’s available in the functools module.





